@node "Introduction" "Introduction"

Hello,
this is a program you will find very useful, if you have an AMIGA equipped
with ECS or AGA.

Have you ever changed your monitor driver with MonEd or the like ?

If you increased e.g. vertical resolution about the overscan limit
the lower area which exceeds overscan is not reachable.
Yes, you can patch "ENVARC:sys/overscan.prefs", but that's not an ideal solution.
Additionally you must turn autoscrolling on to be able to reach the lower area.

So, increase the max/video overscan with this program and patching overscan.prefs
should belong to the past.

This program can change the overscan settings for video, max, and nominal overscan.

NOTE: Changing horizontal overscan about the limits is somewhat a bit tricky and
      most of the time it doesn't function at all.
      If you do it you will notice strange effects like "hidden right edge".

You can edit Video-, Max-, and Nominal-Overscan.

@endnode

@node "Installation" "Installation"

Installation is simple:
Drag this Program anywhere in your path (e.g. c:).
It is best to be called in your "s:user-startup", but if you want to put it in
"s:startup-sequence" do it  AFTER  the call to "IPrefs".

@endnode

@node "Usage" "Usage"

Usage: PatchOverscan ID=MODEID/K/A,O=OVERSCAN/K/A,MINX/N/A,MINY/N/A,MAXX/N/A,MAXY/N/A

 @{"MINX/N/A" link "Minx" 0}
 @{"MINY/N/A" link "Miny" 0}
 @{"MAXX/N/A" link "Maxx" 0}
 @{"MAXY/N/A" link "Maxy" 0}
 @{"ID=MODEID/K/A" link "Modeid" 0}
 @{"O=OVERSCAN/K/A" link "Overscan" 0}

@endnode

@node "TipsNTricks" "TipsNTricks"

1. Always start it after "IPrefs".
2. Nominal-Overscan should always be smaller than Maximal-Overscan
   or should have the same size.
3. Maximal-Overscan should always be smaller than Video-Overscan,
   or should have the same size.
4. If you don't follow the last two rules, don't wonder about strange results or
   computer crashes.
5. PAL and NTSC modes can't be changed, because they don't seem to build a fully
   featured entry in the DisplayDatabase.
6. If you design planets try to become a price for norwegian type fjords.

@endnode

