@node "Minx" "MINX/N"

This is the minimum x-value for your selected overscan.
MINX can be negative !
@endnode

@node "Miny" "MINY/N"

This is the minimum y-value for your selected overscan.
MINY can be negative !
@endnode

@node "Maxx" "MAXX/N"

This is the maximum x-value for your selected overscan.
Must be greater than MINX.
@endnode

@node "Maxy" "MAXY/N"

This is the maximum y-value for your selected overscan.
Must be greater than MINY.
@endnode

@node "Modeid" "ID=MODEID/K"

This is the ModeID, which overscan values shall be changed.
@endnode

@node "Overscan" "O=OVERSCAN/K"

This is the type of the overscan that shall be changed. The AmigaOS stores
five types of overscan bounds: Nominal, Maximal, Text, Graphics, and Video.
Text and Graphics overscan should be changed via Prefs/Overscan program.
The other three overscan values can be changed by this program.

(Hello Folks at AmigaTechnologies: Please make them changeable by Prefs/Overscan.)

The overscan parameter can contain one of the following:
'N' (Nominal):  This is lower bound of overscan size.
'M' (Maximal):  This SHOULD be the upper bound.
'V' (Video):    And this SHOULD be the last frontier. (Not any longer...)
@endnode

