@node "Examples" "Examples"

1. "Super72":

   "PatchOverscan ID=89020 OVERSCAN=N 0 0 699 499"
   "PatchOverscan ID=89024 OVERSCAN=N 0 0 699 999"
   "PatchOverscan ID=89020 OVERSCAN=M 0 0 831 511"
   "PatchOverscan ID=89024 OVERSCAN=M 0 0 831 1023"

   What does it mean ?

   ID=89020 means Super72:SuperHighRes
   ID=89024 means Super72:SuperHighRes Interlace

   (look for my program "ModeIDList" in the same archive)

   The nominal (lower) overscan for ModeID 89020 is set to 700*500.
   For ModeID 89024 it is set to 700*1000.
   The maximum overscan for ModeID 89020 is set to 832*512.
   For ModeID 89024 is it set to 832*1024.

   From now with this settings on you can edit overscan for ModeID 89024
   between 700*1000 and 832*1024 pixels via Prefs/Overscan.
   And you can edit overscan for ModeID 89020 between 700*500 and 832*512
   pixels via Prefs/Overscan.

2. More examples:

   "PatchOverscan ID=39024 O=N 0 0 479 411"
   means: MULTISCAN:Productivity, nominal overscan, 480*412 pixel

   "PatchOverscan ID=39024 O=M 0 0 679 511"
   means: MULTISCAN:Productivity, maximal overscan, 680*512 pixel

   ... and both together means:
   call "Prefs/Overscan", edit MULTISCAN between 480*412 and 680*512 pixel



   "PatchOverscan ID=A9004 O=N 0 0 479 411"
   means: DBLPAL:HighRes no flicker, nominal overscan, 480*412 pixel

   "PatchOverscan ID=A9004 O=M 0 0 779 599"
   means: DBLPAL:HighRes No Flicker, maximal overscan, 780*600 pixel

   ... and both together means:
   call "Prefs/Overscan", edit DBLPAL between 480*412 and 780*600 pixel



   "PatchOverscan ID=99004 O=N 0 0 479 411"
   means: DBLNTSC:HighRes NoFlicker, nominal overscan, 480*412 pixel

   "PatchOverscan ID=99004 O=M 0 0 779 511"
   means: DBLNTSC:HighRes NoFlicker, maximal overscan, 780*512 pixel

   "PatchOverscan ID=69024 O=N 0 0 479 311"
   means: (this one is for you)

   "PatchOverscan ID=69024 O=M 0 0 719 499"
   means: (and this too)
@endnode

